      <div class="bio-content">
        <h1>Malayan Tiger</h1>
        <p class="status critically-endangered big">Critically Endangered</p>
        <p><strong>Estimated remaining:</strong> ~200</p>

        <h3>Habitat</h3>
        <p>Tropical rainforests of the Malay Peninsula, including primary and secondary forests, hill forests, and some agricultural areas in Malaysia and southern Thailand.</p>

        <h3>Threats</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Poaching for illegal wildlife trade</li>
          <li>Habitat fragmentation from palm oil plantations</li>
          <li>Prey depletion due to overhunting</li>
          <li>Road development through forest corridors</li>
          <li>Human-tiger conflict</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Conservation efforts</h3>
        <p>Malaysia's National Tiger Conservation Action Plan aims to double tiger populations by 2022. Increased anti-poaching patrols using SMART technology. Habitat connectivity projects create wildlife corridors between fragmented forests.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
